claim.claim-text:
1. A transflective reflective liquid crystal device comprising 
liquid crystals; 
an upper substrate formed on the liquid crystals; 
an lower substrate formed under the liquid crystals so as to face to the upper substrate; 
an upper polarizing layer formed between the upper substrate and the liquid crystals; 
a reflective polarizing layer formed between the liquid crystals and the lower substrate and having a transparent axis and a reflective axis; 
a lower polarizing layer formed between the lower reflective polarizing layer and the lower substrate; and 
a lighting device: 
wherein a liquid crystal panel comprises the upper substrate, the upper polarizing layer, the liquid crystal, the lower reflective polarizing layer, the lower polarizing layer, and the lower substrate; 
the lighting device is arranged outside of the liquid crystal panel; 
the transparent axis and the reflective axis are orthogonal on the lower reflective polarizing layer; 
the lower reflective polarizing layer is transflective and reflective; 
the lower reflective polarizing layer reflects a part of light which is parallel with a reflective axis and incident and transmits a part of light which is parallel with a reflective axis; 
displaying operation is performed by changing between a transparent mode and a reflection mode.

2. A transflective reflective liquid crystal device comprising 
liquid crystals; 
an upper substrate formed on the liquid crystals; 
an lower substrate formed under the liquid crystals so as to face to the upper substrate; 
an upper polarizing layer formed between the upper substrate and the liquid crystals; 
a reflective polarizing layer formed partly between the liquid crystals and the lower substrate and having a transparent axis and a reflective axis; 
a lower polarizing layer formed between the lower reflective polarizing layer and the lower substrate; and 
a lighting device: 
wherein the lighting device is arranged outside of the lower substrate; 
the transparent axis and the reflective axis are orthogonal on the lower reflective polarizing layer; 
displaying operation is performed by changing between a transparent mode and a reflection mode.
